==Japanese==
=== Etymology ===
{{ja-kanjitab-top}}
! [[金]] || [[曜]] || [[日]]
{{ja-kanjitab-bottom}}
From Latin ''[[dies Veneris]]'' ("day of Venus") through Indian astrology in the fifth century as Sanskrit ''[[bhṝguvāra]]'' (''bhṝgu'', "of the planet Venus") into Buddhist astrology in the eighth century as 金曜日: [[金]] (きん, ''kin'', "gold", the Buddhist element associated with the planet Venus) + [[曜日]] (ようび, ''yōbi'', "day of the week").

===Noun===
{{janoun|きんようび|kinyōbi}}
# [[Friday]]

====Synonyms====
* [[金曜]]

